  "body": "**Is this a BUG REPORT or FEATURE REQUEST?**:\r\n/kind bug\r\n\r\n**What happened**:\r\n\r\nIf a pod is already running in the default namespace with the expected name (i.e. `recycler-for-VOL`), the PV recycle method just assumes it's a recycler pod. However, if it is not a recycler, it could result in the volume being reused without the data being cleared.\r\n\r\n**What you expected to happen**:\r\n\r\nThe recycled volume should not be reused until the data has been verifiably deleted. The easiest approach would be to make it an error to not run the recycler pod successfully, i.e. delete these lines:\r\nhttps://github.com/kubernetes/kubernetes/blob/master/pkg/volume/util.go#L83-L85\r\nI think that should be safe, since the recycler will retry.\r\n\r\nOther errors in that method should also be considered fatal, e.g.:\r\nhttps://github.com/kubernetes/kubernetes/blob/master/pkg/volume/util.go#L92\r\n",
